A Ugandan businessman was yesterday charged in a Nairobi court with unlawfully accessing Safaricom&rsquo;s protected system. Ronald Nsale denied the charges before Milimani chief magistrate Francis Andayi . The court heard between December 1, 2016, and March 30, 2017, at Kilimani, Nairobi county, the accused jointly with others committed the offence. He was released on Sh200,000 bond with a surety of similar amount or a cash bail of the same amount. The prosecution said between January 20 and March 30, 2017, Safaricom IT expert noticed suspicious attempts to access the telco&rsquo;s networks remotely from one of their staff members line. The matter was reported to the senior manager fraud investigation. Parliament police station investigated and suspects were traced to Kilimani and arrested. The case will be heard on May 23.